, pl. 10, figs 3–7) as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC268B1E4A1FB3C92B5" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[1012,1202,153,179]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC268B1E4A1FB3C92B5" box="[1012,1202,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Blountia mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not appear to be conspecific with the 
<typeStatus id="54E56283FFA5FFC26A38E485FE5192D1" box="[381,479,189,215]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">holotype</typeStatus>
and represent a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26860E486FC1292D1" authorityName="Westrop &amp; Eoff" authorityYear="2020" box="[805,924,189,215]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angelae">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26860E486FCB892D1" box="[805,822,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26806E485FC1292D1" box="[835,924,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">angelae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pl. 15). These species are differentiated most clearly by pygidial morphology: the pygidium of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26997E4D9FCC292FC" authorityName="Westrop &amp; Eoff" authorityYear="2020" box="[722,844,224,251]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angelae">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26997E4D9FD6D92FC" box="[722,739,225,250]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC269B6E4D8FCC292FC" box="[755,844,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">angelae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a clearly defined border furrow on both testate surfaces (Pl. 15, fig. 6) and internal moulds (Pl. 15, figs 7–9), whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC268F6E53DFBA89318" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[947,1062,260,287]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC268F6E53DFC4A9318" box="[947,964,261,286]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26897E53CFBA89318" box="[978,1062,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is effaced (Pl. 1, figs 1–3. 9, 10). Cranidia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26A58E511FE1B9344" authorityName="Westrop &amp; Eoff" authorityYear="2020" box="[285,405,296,322]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angelae">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26A58E511FEA09344" box="[285,302,297,322]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26A79E510FE1B9344" box="[316,405,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">angelae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC2695BE511FD1F9344" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[542,657,296,322]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC2695BE511FDA19344" box="[542,559,297,322]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26978E510FD1F9344" box="[573,657,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in frontal area proportions: the anterior border is noticeably longer in the former (compare Pl. 1, figs 1, 5 with Pl. 15, figs 1, 4). In addition, the palpebral areas are wider in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26E61E574FA139360" authorityName="Westrop &amp; Eoff" authorityYear="2020" box="[1316,1437,332,358]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angelae">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26E61E574FABB9363" box="[1316,1333,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26E01E574FA139360" box="[1348,1437,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">angelae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare Pl. 1, fig. 5 and Pl. 15, figs 1, 4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1DC21FFA5FFC26B82E5ACFEB990C8" blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1150]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Cranidia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26A13E5ACFD1093A8" authority="Resser, 1938" authorityName="Resser" authorityYear="1938" box="[342,670,404,430]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bristolensis">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26A13E5ACFE7593A8" box="[342,507,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B. bristolensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCFA1D0FFA5FFC26943E5ACFD1093A8" author="Resser, C. E." box="[518,670,404,430]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 140" refId="ref23917" refString="Resser, C. E. (1938) The Cambrian (Restricted) of the southern Appalachians. Geological Society of America Special Papers, 15, 1 - 140." type="journal article" year="1938">Resser, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, including its synonyms 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26883E5ACFAE693A8" authority="Resser, 1938" authorityName="Resser" authorityYear="1938" box="[966,1384,404,430]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Maryvillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bristolensis">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26883E5ACFB4693A8" box="[966,1224,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Maryvillia bristolensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCFA1D0FFA5FFC26F91E5ACFAE693A8" author="Resser, C. E." box="[1236,1384,404,430]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 140" refId="ref23917" refString="Resser, C. E. (1938) The Cambrian (Restricted) of the southern Appalachians. Geological Society of America Special Papers, 15, 1 - 140." type="journal article" year="1938">Resser, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26BD2E580FCCB93D4" authority="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan, 1944" authorityName="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan" authorityYear="1944" box="[151,837,440,466]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nixonensis">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26BD2E580FEF893D7" box="[151,374,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Blountia nixonensis</emphasis>
Lochman, in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCFA1D0FFA5FFC26953E580FCCB93D4" author="Lochman, C. &amp; Duncan, D." box="[534,837,440,466]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 172" refId="ref23573" refString="Lochman, C. &amp; Duncan, D. (1944) Early Upper Cambrian faunas of Central Montana. Geological Society of America Special Papers, 54, 1 - 172. https: // doi. org / 10.1130 / SPE 54 - p 1" type="journal article" year="1944">Lochman &amp; Duncan, 1944</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see below), have anterior branches of the facial sutures that are subparallel, or nearly so (e.g., Pl. 2, Pl. 3, fig. 5), whereas as those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26F13E5E4FB4593F0" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[1110,1227,476,502]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26F13E5E4FBE993F3" box="[1110,1127,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26F32E5E4FB4593F0" box="[1143,1227,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more strongly diveregent (e.g., Pl. 1, fig. 5). The frontal area of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26984E638FCBA901C" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[705,820,512,538]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26984E638FD5C901F" box="[705,722,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC269A5E638FCBA901C" box="[736,820,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is longer (29% total cranidial length compared to 23% in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26BF1E61CFEDB9038" authorityName="Resser" authorityYear="1938" box="[180,341,548,574]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Maryvillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bristolensis">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26BF1E61CFF4B903B" box="[180,197,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26B91E61CFEDB9038" box="[212,341,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">bristolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the palpebral area of the fixigena is distinctly narrower (compare Pls 2, 4 with Pl. 1, figs 1, 5). Pygidial contrasts are even stronger, with the firmly impressed border furrows of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26F0FE670FB649064" authorityName="Resser" authorityYear="1938" box="[1098,1258,584,610]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Maryvillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bristolensis">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26F0FE670FBD59067" box="[1098,1115,584,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26F2CE670FB649064" box="[1129,1258,584,610]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">bristolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pl. 3, figs 1, 2, Pl. 5) clearly differing from the effaced condition of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC2699AE654FCDF9080" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[735,849,620,646]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC2699AE654FD7E9083" box="[735,752,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC269B8E654FCDF9080" box="[765,849,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The articulated specimens of both 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26F98E654FAC19080" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[1245,1359,620,646]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26F98E654FB609083" box="[1245,1262,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26FBEE654FAC19080" box="[1275,1359,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26EC1E654FE9690AC" authorityName="Resser" authorityYear="1938" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Maryvillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bristolensis">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26EC1E654FA1B9083" box="[1412,1429,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26BD2E6A8FE9690AC" box="[151,280,656,682]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">bristolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have seven thoracic segments, but the latter species has a wider axis (38% of thorax width versus 30% in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26BF1E68CFEA990C8" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[180,295,692,718]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26BF1E68CFF4B90CB" box="[180,197,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26B96E68CFEA990C8" box="[211,295,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1DC21FFA5FFC26B82E6E0FE3A9614" blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1150]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Pygidia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26A06E6E0FCEE90F4" authority="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan, 1944" authorityName="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan" authorityYear="1944" box="[323,864,728,754]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cora">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26A06E6E0FEDA90F7" box="[323,340,728,753]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26A27E6E0FE1B90F7" box="[354,405,728,753]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">cora</emphasis>
Lochman, in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCFA1D0FFA5FFC26977E6E0FCEE90F4" author="Lochman, C. &amp; Duncan, D." box="[562,864,728,754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 172" refId="ref23573" refString="Lochman, C. &amp; Duncan, D. (1944) Early Upper Cambrian faunas of Central Montana. Geological Society of America Special Papers, 54, 1 - 172. https: // doi. org / 10.1130 / SPE 54 - p 1" type="journal article" year="1944">Lochman &amp; Duncan, 1944</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Pilgrim Formation of 
<collectingRegion id="499A12C3FFA5FFC26F8CE6E0FAA190F4" box="[1225,1327,728,754]" country="United States of America" name="Montana" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Montana</collectingRegion>
, show effacement of the border furrow that resembles the condition in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC2680BE6C4FC4F9110" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[846,961,764,790]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC2680BE6C4FCD19113" box="[846,863,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26828E6C4FC4F9110" box="[877,961,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare Pl. 1, figs 3, 9 with Pl. 6, figs 8, 9 and Pl. 7, figs 9, 10, 14). If the 
<typeStatus id="54E56283FFA5FFC2694AE718FDF4913C" box="[527,634,800,826]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">paratypes</typeStatus>
are assigned correctly, the pygidium of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26F05E718FB1C913F" authorityName="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan" authorityYear="1944" box="[1088,1170,800,826]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cora">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26F05E718FBDF913F" box="[1088,1105,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26F1AE718FB1C913F" box="[1119,1170,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">cora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lengthens considerably during holaspid ontogeny (e.g. compare Pl. 6, fig. 9 and Pl. 7, fig. 9). At a similar size, pygidia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26FB8E77CFAFC9158" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[1277,1394,836,862]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26FB8E77CFA80915B" box="[1277,1294,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26E5BE77CFAFC9158" box="[1310,1394,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are relatively longer (e.g., compare Pl. 1, fig. 3 and Pl. 6, fig. 9). Cranidia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC2688EE750FB939187" authorityName="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan" authorityYear="1944" box="[971,1053,872,898]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cora">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC2688EE750FC529187" box="[971,988,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC268AFE750FB939187" box="[1002,1053,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">cora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also show substantial ontogenetic changes in proportions, with strong positive allometry of the frontal area (e.g., compare Pl. 6, figs 1–7 and Pl. 7, figs 11–13). However similarly-sized cranidia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC269D5E788FD6D91CF" authorityName="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan" authorityYear="1944" box="[656,739,944,969]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cora">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC269D5E788FD6D91CF" box="[656,739,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B. cora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pl. 6, figs 4, 6) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC26896E788FBC991CC" authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[979,1095,944,970]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC26896E788FC6A91CF" box="[979,996,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC268B6E788FBC991CC" box="[1011,1095,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pl. 1, fig. 5) are dramatically different, with the latter having a frontal area that is less than half of the relative length of the former, and a much shorter preglabellar field.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1DC21FFA5FFC26B82E024FDAC9678" blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1150]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Pygidial anatomy also separates 
<taxonomicName id="4C5EA7A2FFA5FFC2697FE024FBEB9630" authority="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan, 1944" authorityName="Lochman, in Lochman &amp; Duncan" authorityYear="1944" box="[570,1125,1052,1078]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janei">
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC2697FE024FDC59633" box="[570,587,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92A0033FFA5FFC2691EE024FD1D9633" box="[603,659,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">janei</emphasis>
Lochman, in 
